## Summary of Findings

### Bug Found: Mobile Mode - Conversation Title Editing Not Working

**Test Environment**: Mobile viewport (375px width) using Chrome DevTools device emulation

**Steps to Reproduce**:
1. Open MinimalChat at http://localhost:5173
2. Switch to mobile viewport (375px width) using Chrome DevTools device emulation
3. Open the conversations panel by clicking the chat icon (speech bubble) in the top right of the header
4. Click or double-click on a conversation title in the conversations list

**Expected Behavior**:
- Clicking/double-clicking on a conversation title should enter edit mode, showing an input field that allows the user to modify the title (similar to how it works in desktop mode where clicking on the title makes it editable)

**Actual Behavior**:
- Single-clicking on the conversation title: Closes the conversations panel (treats it as a "select conversation" action)
- Double-clicking on the conversation title: Also closes the conversations panel (does NOT enter edit mode)
- No input field appears for editing the title in mobile mode

**Desktop Mode Comparison**:
- In desktop mode, clicking/double-clicking on the conversation title in the sidebar makes the title editable (text becomes selectable and editable, allowing the user to type a new title)

**Additional Bugs Observed**:
1. Typo in error message: "conversaton" instead of "conversation" (seen in the error message "An error occurred while generating conversaton title.")
2. API authentication errors (401 Unauthorized) when trying to generate conversation titles - but this is expected in a test environment without valid API keys

**Result**: **FAIL** - The conversation title editing feature does not work in mobile mode. Clicking on the conversation title in the mobile conversations panel only closes the panel without entering an edit state.
